      "span_text": "The deficit must not have been secondary to brain hemorrhage, trauma, tumor, infection, or another identifiable mimic, and must have lasted more than 24 hours (unless death supervened).  Possible: If neither imaging evidence nor clinical signs and symptoms consistent with AIS were documented in the chart, a physician diagnosis of AIS recorded in the chart was counted as a \"possible\" event."
